# 3. ストリートの日常

Live House Staff: Cut it out, you guys!
Boy Rapper A: Shut up!
Boy Rapper B: Stay outta this! Or I'll make you eat dirt!!
Onlookers: Guys, calm down!
Little An: Whoa! They're both so angry...!
Taiga: Yeah, geez... It's pretty early to be this riled up.
Nagi: I don't recognize either of them, and they seem awfully young.
Nagi: Wait, I remember someone saying how there's a new MC battle event taking place today...
Boy Rapper A: Hey, take back what you just said!
Boy Rapper B: What's wrong with calling you what you are?! An amateur!
Little An: Oh no! Th-This looks bad...!
Taiga: At this rate, they'll be trading punches in no time.
Nagi: And they look big for their age. The staff won't have an easy time breaking them up.
Nagi: I'm gonna go talk to them.
Taiga: Sure.
Little An: Wait, what's she gonna do?! Aunt Nagi!
Nagi: Sorry, everyone. Mind letting me through?
Onlookers: Hm? Isn't that...? Nagi?!
Nagi: Honestly, fighting in broad daylight. What exactly happened here?
Boy Rapper A: What's it to you, hag?! Don't interrupt!
Nagi: Hmm... You'd think rappers would choose better words, no? I mean, “hag” and “interrupt” don't really rhyme.
Boy Rapper A: Huh? You making fun of me, lady?
Little An: Uncle Taiga, is she gonna be okay...?! They're so much bigger than her!
Taiga: Relax. This is nothing for her.
Boy Rapper B: You've got nothing to do with this, so stay out of our way!
Nagi: Actually, I have everything to do with this. My prized pupil's trying to sing here, so I'd prefer it if you didn't cause such a big commotion.
Nagi: From what I can tell, it sounds like you aren't happy with how your battle was judged and decided to choose the worst option by picking a fight. Did I miss anything?
Boy Rapper A: Grr...!
Nagi: Aha, bullseye. Hmm... You in the cap. I take it you started it?
Boy Rapper A: Don't blame me! Blame the judge!
Boy Rapper A: Who in their right mind thinks that I lost to that crappy flow?!
Boy Rapper B: What?!
Nagi: Settle down. Or is it too late to get you two to cool off...?
Nagi: Alright, why don't you have a rematch right here...?
Boy Rappers A & B: Huh?
Nagi: Don't give me that look. Rappers should be ready to throw down whenever, right?
Nagi: And I'll be the judge this time. You all want to hear them sing, right?!
Nagi: So, what do you two say? You're not about to turn tail and run in front of all these people... Are you?
Boy Rappers A & B: ...!
Boy Rapper A: Of course not! Just who do you think I am?!
Boy Rapper B: You're going down! Again!
Nagi: Alright, let's get started! Do you know what you're going to sing?
Live House Staff: Y-Yeah...!
Nagi: Okay, show us what you've got!!
Boy Rapper A: Grr...! I'm not letting you have this!
Boy Rapper B: Says you!
Little An: Haha! You've both got this!
Taiga: Nagi, go easy on them. I mean, the police might not intervene at this time of day, but...
Nagi: I know! Don't worry!
Boy Rapper A: ♪——! ——! ——————!
Nagi: Hey, that verse was great! You weren't very eloquent during that fight just now, so it's refreshing to hear that you have a good vocabulary.
Little An: This is awesome! Well, maybe not as awesome as Aunt Nagi♪
Boy Rapper B: Next, my turn! Get ready!
Boy Rappers A & B: Huff... Huff... Huff...
Nagi: You both did great! But I think we have to call it a draw.
Nagi: However, if you're still not satisfied, would you like to do another round?
Boy Rapper A: A-After a quick breather...!
Onlooker A: Then, let us do a battle in the meantime!
Onlooker B: Hey, that sounds fun! Let's go!
Little An: Aunt Nagi, I wanna do a battle too!
Nagi: Okay, how about we do one?
Little An: Really?! Yay!
Taiga: After causing such a big stir too... But I guess kids will be kids. Anyway, I'll just sit back and enjoy the show.
An's Father: Hm? Isn't that...?
Nagi: And the winner is... Taiga!
Little An: Uncle Taiga was so awesome! And super cool!
Nagi: You ended up joining in on the fun after saying that you'd just sit back and watch things unfold.
Taiga: My plan was to spice things up a little, but maybe I went a bit overboard.
Boy Rapper A: That old dude's way too good at rapping! What's going on here?!
Boy Rapper B: Same with the people from the crowd that jumped in partway through...! Even that little kid was totally off the hook!
Taiga: Just where exactly do you think you are right now? This is Vivid Street. Rapping and singing are how we greet each other around here.
Taiga: But if you've learned your lesson, quit fighting like knuckleheads and get good.
Nagi: Exactly. You can win as long as you get the crowd going!
Nagi: I mean, you're both doing this because you love it, right?
Boy Rapper A: W-Well...
Boy Rapper B: Yeah... We are...
An's Father: (They stopped another fight...? Honestly, don't they ever get tired of doing that? Still...)
Little An: Hey, can we go again?! I think I can do better this time!
Nagi: Okay! Let's do another one together!
Little An: Yeah! I'll start!
Little An: ♪——! ————!
An's Father: (I guess it isn't all bad since An looks like she's having fun.)
An's Father: Hey, Nagi, Taiga!
Little An: Hi, Daddy!
Nagi: Oh, you're finally here. You came so late that you missed our little event.
An's Father: Sorry about that. But you decided to put on an event before our actual one?
Little An: What's wrong with that?! It's not like we get to hear RADder rap every day!
Boy Rapper A: Wait, RADder...? You guys are RADder...?!
Boy Rapper B: W-We're so sorry...!! We had no idea who we'd been talking to...!!
Taiga: Don't apologize to us. You should be telling that to everyone from the live house and all the other participants.
Boy Rapper A: Oh, right... Yes, we'll do that...
Boy Rapper B: Again, we're sorry for causing so much trouble...
Nagi: Yeah, it is important to assert yourself sometimes, but it's just as important to keep a cool head.
Nagi: Still, all jokes aside, you two weren't bad, and you're taking things seriously enough to fight about it.
Nagi: So, we'll be looking forward to seeing how you both do moving forward!
Boy Rappers A & B: Th-Thank you...!
Little An: Hehe. I'm really glad they stopped fighting!
An's Father: Me too. Also, An, your rapping has improved a lot. Practicing every day is really starting to pay off.
Little An: I know, right?! Hold on. More importantly...!
Little An: Daddy, where were you?! You said you'd watch me practice, but it's already noon!
An's Father: Yeah, sorry about that... Things sort of just dragged on.
An's Father: But I promise to watch you practice tomorrow morning. It's Sunday, so I should be able to stay with you until noon.
Little An: Wait, really?
An's Father: Yeah. And to make up for what happened, you can sit in the VIP section during today's event.
Little An: Whoa! Are you sure?!
An's Father: Yes, there's going to be an opening it seems and the manager personally requested you fill that seat.
Little An: Woohoo!! Thank you so much, Daddy!
An's Father: You're welcome. Anyway, let's get going.
